{"word":"λογοποιός","slug":"λογοποιός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λογοποιός</b></el> <el>(λογο-ποιός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ποιέω'><el>ποιέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a prose-writer</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>an historian, chronicler</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a writer of fables</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:λογογράφος'><el>λογογράφος</el></a> II, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a tale-teller, newsmonger</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}